<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Discovery Ridge</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Development of Discovery Ridge real estate began in the 1990s, prior to which the area was an isolated valley referred to as “Jackson’s Valley” or New Discovery by locals. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The southwest quadrant of Calgary features the scenic residential community of Discovery Ridge. The community is flanked by Glenmore Trail on the north and to the east by 69th Street. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The average sale price for homes in Discovery Ridge real estate is around $770,000. Options for homes are plenty and the pricing tends to be in the mid-high range for single family homes between $252,000 and $1,250,000. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Discovery Ridge real estate feature architecturally designed modern homes with great amenities and serene, picturesque locales. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">On the Southwest corner of Calgary at the Edge of Glenmore Trail and Sarcee Trail South, just minutes from Downtown Calgary lies the secluded Calgary real estate community of Discovery Ridge. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Homes in Discovery Ridge enjoy a backdrop of pine trees and mountain views. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The Elbow river rushes nearby and this charming area is reminiscent of an inner-city Canmore. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Discovery Ridge homes range from small forest edge condominiums and field-backed villas to gorgeous Discovery Ridge estate homes. </p>
        </div>
